!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

dependent /dɪˈpɛndənt/

1. ADJ To be dependent on something or someone means to need them in order to succeed or be able to survive. 依靠的 

例： The local economy is overwhelmingly dependent on oil and gas extraction. 当地经济严重依赖石油和天然气提炼。 

2. ADJ If one thing is dependent on another, the first thing will be affected or determined by the second. 取决于…的 [v-link ADJ 'on/upon' n] 

例： ...companies whose earnings are largely dependent on the performance of the Chinese economy. …盈利很大程度上取决于中国经济表现的公司。 

3. N-COUNT Dependent is the same as . 同dependant [美国英语]

</div>

